Security ethics:
                Guidelines and makinng appropriate decisions as a security professional.

Ethical Principles in security:
                          1) Confidentiality
                          2) Privacy protection
                          3) Laws

1) Confidentiality in ethics: Confidentiality means that only authorized users can access specific assets or data. Confidentiality as it relates to professional ethics means that there needs to be a high level of respect for privacy to safeguard private assets and data. 
                              Keep your PII data priivate as a data analyst of particular organization.

2) Privacy Protection: Safeguarding Personal infrmation from unauthorized use.
                     Personally identifiable information (PII) and sensitive personally identifiable information (SPII) are types of personal data that can cause people harm if they are stolen. PII data is any information used to infer an individual's identity, like their name and phone number. SPII data is a specific type of PII that falls under stricter handling guidelines, including social security numbers and credit card numbers. To effectively safeguard PII and SPII data, security professionals hold an ethical obligation to secure private information, identify security vulnerabilities, manage organizational risks, and align security with business goals. 

3) Laws: Laws are that are recognized by a community annd enforced by a governing entity. 
         As a security professional, you will have an ethical obligation to protect your organization, its internal infrastructure, and the people involved with the organization. To do this:
              l) You must remain unbiased and conduct your work honestly, responsibly, and with the highest respect for the law. 

              ll) Be transparent and just, and rely on evidence.

              lll) Ensure that you are consistently invested in the work you are doing, so you can appropriately and ethically address issues that arise. 

              lV) Stay informed and strive to advance your skills, so you can contribute to the betterment of the cyber landscape. 
